{
  "stem": "2002.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 103.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And as my brothers and sisters grew up, my brother started to be also in the same business, but he was very respectful and very liked by the people.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of peddlin'.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Being a peddler.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] did already a-- a better style of business.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The people liked him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So as he started to make a living, he already started to get my mother some money for food for the other family.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Also, one brother moved-- went to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he started to work there as a tailor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as I understood, that he was living on bread and coffee, or tea and butter.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He wouldn't go out to eat, because he want to save every penny when it came to a holiday to bring some money that we could have a holiday to buy food.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he even brought home for my father and my mother some clothing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So as we got older, things started to improve.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As the older children started working--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As-- That's right.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--and helping out.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Things started to improve.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were not religious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Let's put that way, according to the United States, [LAUGHS] we were all religious.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But according to my father we were not religious.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't do little things that we did, we shouldn't do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we do believed in God, but not as extreme as-- I remember I went to one of the villages where my father was dealing.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the Christian family was very happy when they gave me some non-kosher food to eat, like bacon or ham.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I'd-- I'd been so hungry I would eat anything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they were happy that they took a Jew, they made him non-kosher.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But in terms of observances, you were-- when you were growing up, were you going to shul?",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
